<HEAD>Panamanian-Registered Freighter Capsizes, Killing Two Filipino Crewmen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Japanese military helicopters rescued all 20
Filipino sailors Wednesday morning after their freighter sank in
rough seas in the East China Sea, but two later died at a hospital,
a local coast guard official said.
   The two dead, deckhands on the 6,034-ton, Panamanian-registered
Tyche, were among eight crew members picked up by a Self Defense
Forces helicopter after they abandoned the flooded vessel 110 miles
