<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Nigeria-Saudi     11-15 0102</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Nigeria-Saudi,0105</SECOND>
<HEAD>Saudis Deport 400 Nigerians</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Saudi Arabia deported 400 Nigerians,
putting them on a flight to Kano in northern Nigeria, a newspaper
reported Wednesday.
   The Nigerians were sent home Tuesday on a special flight of the
Saudi national airline, according to the independent Punch
newspaper.
   The 400 included men and women who had been living in Saudi
Arabia illegally for years. The newspaper said more than 1,000
other Nigerians were sent home earlier this year.
   Most of the Nigerians had gone to Saudi Arabia on pilgrimages to
Mecca and elected to remain there, the newspaper said.
</TEXT>
