<SECOND>AM-BRF--Mexico-Batman,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Batman Forgers Foiled, 18 Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested 18 people on charges of
selling counterfeit Batman clothes, posters and accessories with
the comic book hero's logotype, the Attorney General's office said
Wednesday.
   According to a communique from the Attorney General's office,
the people produced fake Batman products and distributed them to
stores and street markets throughout Mexico City. The movie
``Batman'' has been a hit since it opened here two months ago, and
T-shirts and other Batman products are hot sellers.
   Police seized 39,000 counterfeit T-shirts, another 20,000
Batman-related products as well as stamping and decal-making
equipment and presses for clothing. The souvenirs also included
buttons, notebooks and bottle openers.
   Seven businesses were closed, the communique said.
   Police raided the businesses after the only legal Batman
concessionaire in Mexico filed a complaint, the statement said.
