<FIRST>r i AM-StLucia-Death     11-15 0262</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-St Lucia-Death,0269</SECOND>
<HEAD>American Tourist Hacked to Death in St. Lucia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CASTRIES, St. Lucia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American tourist was hacked to
death when a man with a history of mental illness attacked her as
she was hiking up a mountain on this Caribbean island, authorities
said Wednesday.
   The Tourist Board said Leroy McDoom, who according to police was
mentally ill, on Tuesday fatally cut Judith Taylor with a machete
in the southwestern town of Soufriere, 26 miles from Castries.
   Ms. Taylor, in her 30s, unmarried and believed to be a dual
citizen of the United States and West Germany, suffered a severed
arm and died shortly after the attack. Her hometown was not
immediately known, the Tourist Board said.
   She was with a group of six tourists attempting to scale the
2,461-foot Petit Piton mountain, a main tourist attraction here.
   ``It is understood that the group divided, Ms. Taylor and a male
companion resting whilst the main group continued,'' the Tourist
Board said in a statement. ``McDoom apparently harassed Ms. Taylor
and her companion who went to seek assitance from the other members
of the group. During his brief absence, Ms. Taylor was attacked and
fatally wounded.''
   McDoom was taken into custody, police said. Charges are pending.
   The incident came exactly one year after a British tourist,
Leonard Wiseman, was shot to death during a holdup at a picnic.
Last month, Hazel Emmanuel, 35, was sentenced to hang for the
murder.
   In 1988, more than 214,000 tourists visited this island of
140,000 people, where tourism is the main foreign exchange-earner.
</TEXT>
