<HEAD>Eds: Members who used PM-Fax News, f0007 of Tuesday, Nov. 14, are
asked to use the following story.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press reported erroneously
Wednesday that USA Today has been selling a facsimile version of
the newspaper.
   USA Today is discussing with MCI Communications Corp. the
possibility of transmitting via facsimile machine 18 supplemental
news roundups now available through a computer linkup.
   USA Today had made available those services plus a one-page news
and sports summary transmitted the same morning as the newspaper
through outside facsimile networks, but those deals ended earlier
this year, said Phil Fuhrer, vice president of Gannett New Media,
the research and development division of USA Today owner Gannett
Co. Inc.
</TEXT>
