<HEAD>The New England Names New President</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert A. Shafto, head of The New England's
insurance operation, has been elected president and chief operating
officer of the Boston-based life insurance and financial services
firm.
   Edward E. Phillips, chairman and chief executive officer of The
New England, also said Wednesday that Ralph F. Verni has been named
president and chief executive of New England Investment Companies
Inc., a holding company for all of the investment management
subsidiaries of The New England.
   Shafto and Verni will report directly to Phillips.
   Phillips said John A. Fibiger, president, chief operating
officer and vice chairman of The New England, will take early
retirement at the end of the year. The investment management
holding company, headed by Verni, will be comprised of: Copley Real
Estate Advisors, Loomis, Sayles and Co., Capital Growth Managment,
Back Bay Advisors, New England Securities Corp., Marlborough
Capital Advisors, Boylston Capital Advisor, and New England
Institutional Marketing Inc.
